<h2 class="page-headline">TextField Component</h2>
<p>
    The <code>TextField</code> component can be used to update and display a models value.
    It creates a two-way data binding between the model and the component.
    To connect the component with the markup its <code>component-id</code> has to be set on an according HTML tag.
    <br /><br />
    Usage: <code> new TextField(componentId, modelProperty, model) </code>
<ul>
    <li>
        The 1st parameter is the the component identifier.
    </li>
    <li>
        The 2nd parameter is the key of the model property it should be bound to.
    </li>
    <li>
        The 3rd parameter is the model bound to the component
    </li>
</ul>
</p>


<div class="panel panel-material-purple">
    <div class="panel-heading">
        <div class="panel-title">Example</div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
        <form class="form-horizontal" role="form">
            <fieldset>
                <legend>Example</legend>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="inputName" class="col-lg-2 control-label">Name</label>

                    <div class="col-lg-10">
                        <div class="form-control-wrapper">
                            <input class="form-control" type="email" component-id="textfield" id="inputName" placeholder="Name">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="inputName" class="col-lg-2 control-label">Actual Value</label>

                    <div class="col-lg-10">
                        <div class="form-control-wrapper">
                            <span component-id="textfieldValue"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </fieldset>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>

